        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 5:24PM MDT by NWS Riverton WY</headline>
        <description>At 524 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ralston, which is 11 miles west of Powell, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Ralston around 530 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
